Alert Management Practise:
I created an alert classification system using Microsoft Excel to organize and prioritize security alerts based on severity type and MITRE ATT&CK mapping The sheet 
was designed to 
simulate how alerts are structured and analyzed in a real SOC environment

Purpose:

The purpose of this sheet is to standardize alert handling by mapping different types of security events to their corresponding MITRE ATT&CK techniques This helps 
in improving alert triage prioritization and understanding attacker behavior

Structure of the Sheet:

The Excel sheet includes key fields such as Alert ID Alert Name Type Source Priority MITRE Tactic MITRE Technique Description and Recommended Action These fields 
help in categorizing alerts and providing clear response guidance

Implementation:

I added multiple alerts such as phishing brute force malware execution privilege escalation and data exfiltration Each alert was assigned a priority level based on 
impact and likelihood and mapped to relevant MITRE techniques such as T1566 for phishing and T1059 for command execution

Usage:

This sheet can be used by SOC analysts to quickly identify the severity of alerts understand the attack technique and take appropriate response actions It also
helps in maintaining consistency in alert handling and improving investigation efficiency

Key Learning:

Through this task I learned how to structure and prioritize alerts how MITRE ATT&CK mapping enhances threat analysis and how standardized classification improves 
SOC workflow efficiency
